<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-06-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-06-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="96" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89France/132: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-06-23T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                            1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>235. Your 336, June 18, 6 p.m. Reference your first paragraph. I
                                would be glad if you can find it possible to suggest that in speech
                                on July 3 intention be publicly announced of sending commission to
                                Washington to enter upon debt-funding negotiations, and that an
                                early date be set for commission’s departure.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>